@tdms I've been trying to remember why we added the wildcards. There was a legal character in image names that we needed a greedy capture to include and gorilla mux by default did not include. Caused unexpected 404's as the there was no match.

The change propagated into comments so everything matched. 

Is this a stylistic change you want or is this blocking some tool?

@tmds my apologies, I didn't realize you were waiting on me (because I don't understand this conversation thread at all).

If the goal is to remove dot-star from the comments, but leave it in the declaration thingies, please apply the following:
```diff
diff --git a/hack/swagger-check b/hack/swagger-check
index d20318305..45832d77d 100755
--- a/hack/swagger-check
+++ b/hack/swagger-check
@@ -186,9 +186,10 @@ sub handle_handle {
         or die "$ME: $path:$.: Cannot grok '$line'\n";
     my $endpoint = $1;

-    # FIXME: in older code, '{name:..*}' meant 'nameOrID'. As of 2020-02
-    # it looks like most of the '{name:..*}' entries are gone, except for one.
-###FIXME-obsolete?    $endpoint =~ s|\{name:\.\.\*\}|{nameOrID}|;
+    # Some function declarations require an argument of the form '{name:.*}'
+    # but the swagger comment itself can't have ':.*', some sort of tool
+    # thingy chokes on them (#9121). Normalize all such args to just '{name}'.
+    $endpoint =~ s/\{name:\.\*\}/\{name\}/;

     # e.g. /auth, /containers/*/rename, /distribution, /monitor, /plugins
     return 1 if $line =~ /\.UnsupportedHandler/;
```
Please revise the comment to be more meaningful to someone swagger-literate (and perhaps also be readable by those of us who are clueless).

Big request: you need to rebase, but please wait until #9952 merges before you re-push. Thank you.
